# =============================================================================
# Learning Navigator - Application Requirements
# =============================================================================

App Name: Learning Navigator
Version: 1.0.0

# =============================================================================
# User Roles & Permissions
# =============================================================================

Administrator Role:
    - manages user accounts and permissions
    - has all permissions of a learning navigator
    - oversees the overall functioning of the application

Student Role:
    - schedules meetings with learning navigator with initial meeting being a weekly recurrence on the same day and time each week
    - reschedules or cancels their meetings in a calendar view and send notifications to the learning navigator of the change

Learning Navigator Role:
    - they can manage student meetings
    - they can view and edit their own profile information
    - create notes on students
    - during a learning navigatoring session, they can do private notes on the student that only they can see as well as shared notes that are emailed to the student after the session
    - when students book a learning navigatoring session, they will appear on the learning navigator's calendar and the learning navigator will receive a notification
    - learning navigators can view their schedule in a calendar view and manage their availability
    - learning navigators can reschedule or cancel meetings with students in a calendar view; this will notify the student of the change
    - learning navigators can view and manage their students' profiles and notes
    - can generate reports on their learning navigatoring sessions, including student progress and session history for individuals or groups of students

# =============================================================================
# Features
# =============================================================================

Authentication/Authorization:
    - implement secure authentication using Google OAuth for students to create accounts and log in
    - ensure that only authorized users (students and learning navigators) can access their respective features and data
    - implement role-based access control to differentiate between student and learning navigator functionalities
    - only accounts from students.highline.edu should be allowed to register
    - trlandrew@students.highline.edu should be the only account that can register as administrator
    - allow login from local test accounts for development and testing purposes, but ensure that these accounts are not used in production
    - JWT-based session management with configurable expiration (default: 7 days)
    - Passport.js for authentication strategy management

Calendar Integration:
    - integrate with Google Calendar API to allow students and learning navigators to manage their schedules and appointments
    - ensure that scheduled meetings are automatically added to the respective Google Calendars of students and learning navigators
    - provide a calendar view for both students and learning navigators to easily manage their appointments and availability
    - FullCalendar library for interactive calendar UI with day, week, and month views

Notifications:
    - implement email notifications for students and learning navigators when meetings are scheduled, rescheduled, or canceled
    - ensure that notifications include relevant details such as date, time, and any changes made to the meeting
    - provide an option for users to customize their notification preferences (e.g., receive notifications via email or in-app)
    - in-app notification panel with real-time updates

Profile Management:
    - allow students and learning navigators to view and edit their profile information, including name, email, and profile picture
    - ensure that profile updates are reflected across the application and in notifications
    - provide a secure way for users to manage their account settings and preferences

Notes Management:
    - allow learning navigators to create and manage notes on students, including private notes that only they can see and shared notes that are emailed to the student after a session
    - ensure that notes are securely stored and accessible only to authorized users
    - provide a user-friendly interface for learning navigators to create, edit, and view notes on their students

Reporting:
    - allow learning navigators to generate reports on their learning navigatoring sessions, including student progress and session history for individuals or groups of students
    - provide options for exporting reports in various formats (e.g., PDF, Excel)
    - ensure that reports are generated accurately and include relevant data for analysis and tracking of student progress
    - PDFKit for PDF report generation

