# =============================================================================
# Tech Stack
# =============================================================================

Frontend:
    - React.js 18.x for building the user interface and managing state
    - Material-UI (MUI) 5.x for component library and theming
    - React Router 6.x for client-side routing
    - FullCalendar 6.x for calendar views (day, week, month)
    - MUI X Date Pickers for date/time selection
    - Axios for HTTP requests
    - date-fns for date manipulation

Backend:
    - Node.js with Express.js 4.x for handling server-side logic and API endpoints
    - Mongoose 7.x for MongoDB object modeling
    - Passport.js for authentication (Google OAuth 2.0 and local strategy)
    - express-validator for request validation
    - Helmet for security headers
    - CORS for cross-origin resource sharing

Database:
    - MongoDB for storing user data, meetings, notes, and reports
    - MongoDB Atlas (M0 free tier) for cloud database hosting

Authentication:
    - Google OAuth 2.0 for secure user authentication and account management
    - Passport.js with passport-google-oauth20 strategy
    - JWT (jsonwebtoken) for session tokens
    - bcryptjs for password hashing (local accounts)

Calendar Integration:
    - Google Calendar API (googleapis) for managing schedules and appointments

Notifications:
    - Nodemailer for sending email notifications to users
    - Gmail SMTP for email delivery

Report Generation:
    - PDFKit for PDF report generation

# =============================================================================
# Deployment
# =============================================================================

Local Development:
    - Docker containers for easy deployment and scalability
    - docker-compose for managing multi-container applications (MongoDB, server, client)
    - Dockerfile.server for Node.js backend container
    - Dockerfile.client for React frontend container
    - Nodemon for development hot-reloading
    - Concurrently for running server and client simultaneously

Cloud Deployment (Infrastructure as Code with Terraform):
    - MongoDB Atlas (M0 free tier) for cloud database
        - Automatic project and cluster provisioning
        - Database user creation with appropriate roles
        - IP access list configuration for dynamic cloud IPs
    - Render for backend API hosting (free tier)
        - Automatic deployment from GitHub repository
        - Environment variable management
        - Health checks and auto-scaling
    - Vercel for frontend hosting (free tier)
        - Automatic deployment from GitHub repository
        - Edge network CDN
        - Environment variable management

Infrastructure Configuration:
    - Terraform providers: mongodbatlas, render, vercel
    - Required API keys/tokens:
        - MongoDB Atlas: Organization API key with "Organization Project Creator" role
        - Render: API key and owner ID (user or team)
        - Vercel: API token (and optional team ID)
    - Configuration files:
        - infrastructure/main.tf - Provider configuration
        - infrastructure/mongodb-atlas.tf - MongoDB Atlas resources
        - infrastructure/render.tf - Render backend service
        - infrastructure/vercel.tf - Vercel frontend deployment
        - infrastructure/variables.tf - Input variable definitions
        - infrastructure/outputs.tf - Output values
        - infrastructure/terraform.tfvars.example - Example configuration template

Environment Variables:
    Backend (server):
        - NODE_ENV: production/development
        - PORT: Server port (default: 5001 local, 10000 Render)
        - MONGODB_URI: MongoDB connection string
        - SESSION_SECRET: Express session secret
        - JWT_SECRET: JWT signing secret
        - JWT_EXPIRES_IN: Token expiration (default: 7d)
        - GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID: Google OAuth client ID
        - GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET: Google OAuth client secret
        - GOOGLE_CALLBACK_URL: OAuth callback URL
        - EMAIL_HOST: SMTP host (smtp.gmail.com)
        - EMAIL_PORT: SMTP port (587)
        - EMAIL_USER: SMTP username
        - EMAIL_PASSWORD: SMTP password (app password)
        - EMAIL_FROM: Sender email address
        - ADMIN_EMAIL: Administrator email
        - ALLOWED_DOMAIN: Allowed email domain (students.highline.edu)
        - CLIENT_URL: Frontend URL for CORS

    Frontend (client):
        - REACT_APP_API_URL: Backend API URL
        - REACT_APP_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID: Google OAuth client ID

